<h1>General Information - Crypto Library</h1><a href="100">General Information</a><br><br>The Crypto Library provides the encryption, decryption, and hashing functions needed for Encryption Manager to work. Without the library, Encryption Manager will not be able to function correctly.
102
<h1>General Information - Identities</h1><a href="100">General Information</a><br><br>Identities are used to uniquely identify you to others, as well as allowing people to send you messages or data that only you will be able to decrypt. The use of <a href="202">Public Key Encryption</a> allows data to be encrypted for a specific person and self-signing of data, meaning that the sorce of the data can be verified once it is decrypted. The use of Identities allows secure communication between two persons in which only the intended recipient can decrypt and the sender can be verified.
